                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d727">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.00 Statement July 16, 1937/25: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davies</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-07-24T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 24, 1937—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>110. Your 188, July 23, 8 p.m. My plan has been to get the maximum beneficial
                    effect by assembling replies from all governments and publishing them en bloc. I
                    should thus prefer to defer publication and arrange with Moscow for a later
                    simultaneous release, although I do not feel I can insist thereon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
